==English==
===Etymology===
From the name of Caesar Cardini, the restaurateur who invented this salad

===Noun===
'''Caesar [[salad]]''' (''plural'' '''Caesar salads''')

#(''gastronomy'') A salad generally made from [[romaine]] [[lettuce]], [[crouton]]s, [[parmesan cheese]], [[coddled]] or [[hard-boiled]] eggs, fresh-ground [[black pepper]] and [[Worcestershire sauce]].

